# Global page & design requirements

## Design system (mandatory)

Use the **homepage design system only**. Do not introduce alternate palettes, fonts, or component styles.

- **Tokens**: `src/app/globals.css` (`--forest`, `--lime`, `--paper`, `--ink`, shadows, radii, `--ease`)
- **Tailwind**: `@theme` aliases (`bg-dark`, `text-ink-muted`, `text-accent-bright`, etc.)
- **Sections**: `ScrollSection`, `SectionContainer`, `DisplayHeading`, `Eyebrow` from `@/components/ui/scroll-section`
- **Cards**: `BentoCard`, `BentoGrid` from `@/components/ui/bento-card`
- **Actions**: `Button`, `LinkButton`, `MagneticButton` â€” match homepage CTAs
- **Motion**: `Reveal`, `Stagger`, `StaggerChild` from `@/components/client/reveal` (Framer Motion)
- **Icons**: Lucide React only
- **Surfaces**: `hero-forest`, `gradient-light`, `gradient-cta`, `noise`, `orb`, `glass-dark`, `glass-light`, `card-hover`

Page-specific CSS (`src/styles/*.css`) may only extend tokens â€” never new brand colors.

## Content (Ongo â†’ Ideal Physician)

- Extract **factual/legal/medical text** from Ongo Weight Loss pages when building content pages.
- Store copy in `src/lib/constants/*-content.ts`; swap brand to `siteConfig.name` and site contact info.
- **Do not copy Ongo layouts.** Reorganize for readability and hierarchy without changing legal or medical meaning.
- Never paraphrase legal disclaimers, HIPAA, privacy, or terms unless explicitly asked.

## Page structure pattern

```tsx
// app/[route]/page.tsx
export const metadata = createMetadata({ title, description, openGraph });
export default function Page() {
  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <main id="main-content" tabIndex={-1}>
        {/* ScrollSection-based sections */}
        <Footer />
      </main>
    </>
  );
}
```

Legal/info pages: hero â†’ structured sections â†’ contact/CTA. Use reading progress or sticky TOC when content is long.

## Quality bar

- **Responsive**: mobile-first; test `sm` / `lg` breakpoints
- **Accessible**: semantic HTML, labels, focus states, `aria-*`, skip link respected
- **SEO**: `createMetadata()` on every route
- **Performance**: prefer Server Components; `"use client"` only for forms, scroll, accordion
- **Feel**: premium healthcare SaaS â€” bento grids, subtle gradients, glass where homepage uses it, restrained micro-interactions

## Before shipping a new page

1. Reuses existing UI primitives (no one-off button/card styles)
2. Copy lives in constants file, not hardcoded in JSX
3. Footer legal links updated if new policy page
4. `npm run build` passes
